crimson gold ( persian : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) is a 2003 iranian film directed by jafar panahi , and written by abbas kiarostami . the film was never distributed in iranian theatres , because it was considered too " dark " . therefore , it was not possible that crimson gold be considered as the iranian entry for best foreign language film for the 2003 oscars as it was not released in iran .